Dear All,

I am a new user to Cantera.  Using the Matlab version of Cantera 1.6.0
under Red Hat Linux Enterprise edition with kernel 2.6.9 and GCC 3.4.3
and Matlab 7.0.0 on a 3.2 GHz Pentium 4 Xeon.  I am only a Linux user,
and not a developer, so most of the error messages appear mysterious
to me.

Following the instructions, I downloaded Cantera and compiled and
installed it on July 6.  I ran the self-test at that time.  Now I wish
to test the Matlab part of Cantera.  So I navigate in Matlab to
~/cantera-1.6.0/Cantera/matlab/cantera/examples.  Then I open the file
run_examples.m in that subdirectory, and attempt to run it in the
Matlab interpreter.  I get the error message pasted to the end of this
post.  The problem appears related to the version of GCC used to
compile (?) and obtain the ctmethods.mexglx file.  I searched the
archives of this user group for the string "GCC" and I noticed a
thread begun by Michele V. who also had a problem with this file, but
her problem appears to differ from mine in the details.  In my case,
the file exists on the disk in the location specified and has a file
size of 2581107 bytes.

Anyone have any insight into or prior experience with this problem?

Ananda Himansu
